  <text xml:lang="ta">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="Aink54-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">vāyil vēṇṭivanta talaimakaṟkut talaimakaḷ kuṟippaṟinta tōḻi avaṉ koṭumai
          kūṟi vāyil maṟuttatu.
        </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="Aink54">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>tiṇṭērt teṉṉava ṉaṉṉāṭ ṭuḷḷatai</l>
          <l>vēṉi lāyiṉun taṇpuṉa loḻukun</l>
          <l>tēṉū raṉṉaviva ṭerivaḷai nekiḻa</l>
          <l>vūri ṉūraṉai nītara vanta</l>
          <l>pañcāyk kōtai makaḷirk</l>
          <l>kañcuva lamma vammuṟai variṉē</l>
        </lg>


        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">


          <l> If you mount [i.e. drive off in your chariot], </l>
          <l rend="indent2"> so that the clear i.e. shining bangles become loose </l>
          <l rend="indent2"> of this girl who is like Tēṉūr </l>
          <l rend="indent8"> where cool floods flow even in summer</l>
          <l rend="indent8"> [Tēṉūr] situated in the good land of the Southern King with strong
            chariots – </l>
          <l> Alas, I am afraid for the women who come to give [you], the man from the village, Pañcāy grass garlands, </l>
          <l> if you go (lit. come) [to them] in turn/if you go (lit. come) that way.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
